{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'During the prohibition of alcoholic beverages between 1920 and 1930 in the US, there were multiple negative impacts on consumers.'}

{'type': 'con', 'text': "Foreign countries' dealers might find it convenient to resupply in a nearby country where drugs have been legalized, thus boosting the phenomenon of international drug trafficking, expensive to track down and halt."}
{'type': 'con', 'text': 'In some instances, drug use has increased following legalisation. I believe legalization of drugs is a really bad idea.'}

{'type': 'pro', 'text': '[A study](http://aic.gov.au/media_library/publications/tandi_pdf/tandi372.pdf) came to the conclusion that alcohol consumption was involved in 47% of homicides in Australia in a six-year period. I believe legalization of drugs is a pretty good idea.'}
{'type': 'con', 'text': "Lots of drug addicts don't want to use drugs, but they can't just simply choose to stop using drugs, because they have an addiction."}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'The legalization of drugs means that they are taken, and disposed of, more safely and cautiously than in the current environment.'}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'Legalization will allow for effective tools and strategies to fight criminal organizations.'}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': "That's already true in [most states \\(USA\\)](https://www.ghsa.org/state-laws/issues/drug%20impaired%20driving)"}

{'type': 'con', 'text': 'Making it legal for companies to sell and market these drugs for recreational use without an understanding of the negative consequences that these substances cause is unethical. I believe drugs should remain illegal.'}

{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'If these substances legitimately are so dangerous, they _should_ primarily be considered weapons and not drugs. They can then be ignored in this discussion. I think legalization of drugs is a pretty good idea.'}

{'type': 'con', 'text': "Legalisation of cigarettes [did not stop](https://thedebrief.co.uk/news/real-life/1-every-7-british-cigarettes-contraband-counterfeit/) illicit and poor quality cheaper versions. That's why legalization of drugs is a really bad idea."}
{'type': 'con', 'text': 'Legalizing drugs should not be a prerequisite for better education. I think drugs should remain illegal.'}
{'type': 'con', 'text': 'Without proper education, people who are more prone to drug addiction may be more likely to get addicted to a drug.'}
{'type': 'con', 'text': 'Some drugs are toxic at very low doses. These drugs can rightfully be considered weapons as well as intoxicants.'}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': '[The human right to personal autonomy](http://www.corteidh.or.cr/tablas/r26750.pdf) should include the freedom to take drugs.'}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'The human body is very complex; a given drug can have quite subtle aspects. I believe all drugs should be legal.'}

{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'Legalization will lead to increased import/export options for medicines/drugs that are only available overseas and that were banned in the domestic market. I believe legalization of drugs is a pretty good idea.'}

{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'A [2018 poll](https://sputniknews.com/analysis/201809141068019139-uk-drugs-policy-children-threat/) reported that children find it easier to acquire illegal substances than legal ones.'}

{'type': 'con', 'text': "The ability to alter another person's mind state has potential for abuse, and utter manipulation. As a result, people will be more able to infringe on the bodily freedom/autonomy of others."}

{'type': 'pro', 'text': '[Ketamine](https://www.medicalnewstoday.com/articles/322534.php?iacp), a promising alternative to opioids, is currently banned. I believe legalization of drugs is a pretty good idea.'}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'If the government cannot take responsibility for a dangerous activity which takes place in society, there is no guarantee anyone else will.'}

{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'Sobriety may be required for the optimal exercise of rational moral agency; however, it is not required for the generell exercise of rational moral agency. So legalization of drugs is a pretty good idea.'}
{'type': 'con', 'text': 'Cocaine, a commonly-used illegal drug, has [multiple negative health effects](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Cocaine_intoxication) on the user.'}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'The same applies to already legal alcohol. I think all drugs should be legal.'}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': "Someone experiencing elevated stress levels isn't a good enough justification to limit other people's freedom by force. So legalization of drugs is a pretty good idea."}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'Legalization will help patients by facilitating access to medicines \\(drugs\\) that are currently hard to obtain. I think all drugs should be legal.'}

{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'The consumption of psychoactive substances creates religious and transcendental [experiences](https://www.sciencealert.com/how-religion-led-to-humanity-s-love-for-drugs): both are a relevant part of human evolution and significantly shaped human culture. I believe all drugs should be legal.'}

{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'There have been [no positive consequences](http://fileserver.idpc.net/library/Shadow%20Report_FINAL_ENGLISH.pdf) as a result of the war on drugs. I believe legalization of drugs is a pretty good idea.'}

{'type': 'con', 'text': 'Although not all people are affected in this way, the risk for psychosis is higher [when regularly consuming cannabis with a high concentration of THC.](https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pmc/articles/PMC2801827/)'}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'Strict quality controls will stimulate a fair competition amongst drug suppliers to offer the purest drugs. I believe legalization of drugs is a pretty good idea.'}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'Drugs are insanely profitable at a relatively low level of effort, as opposed to other crimes.'}

{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'It is possible that decriminalization dissuades those who specifically start using drugs as a way of breaking the law, such as [early data from Portugal](https://www.leafly.com/news/politics/portugal-drug-decriminalization-statistics) suggests. I think all drugs should be legal.'}

{'type': 'pro', 'text': "In the US, incarceration reduces former inmates' earnings by [40 percent](https://www.pewtrusts.org/en/research-and-analysis/reports/0001/01/01/collateral-costs) on average and limits their future economic mobility."}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': "The issue is not drug legalization, but the functioning of the health insurances. That's why legalization of drugs is a pretty good idea."}

{'type': 'con', 'text': 'Colorado has seen a "[slight increase](https://www.colorado.gov/pacific/cdphe/marijuana-use-2017)" in the number of adult marijuana users in the period 2014-2017 following legalisation. I believe drugs should remain illegal.'}

{'type': 'pro', 'text': "Decriminalization would encourage the implementation of a broader scope of impairment detection devices. This would cause users to think twice about driving impaired on substances they believe wouldn't be detected using current methods. I think all drugs should be legal."}

{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'The increased tax revenue could enable increased government spending, which [results in more jobs](https://www.americanprogress.org/issues/economy/reports/2011/09/08/10257/government-spending-can-create-jobs-and-it-has/).'}

{'type': 'con', 'text': 'Legalisation will at length normalize drug use, which can lead to excess use as with alcohol \\(drinking games, binge drinking\\) which can be far more dangerous when done with hard drugs.'}

{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'Drug prohibition has lead to [high incarceration rates](https://www.politifact.com/truth-o-meter/statements/2016/jul/10/cory-booker/how-war-drugs-affected-incarceration-rates/) of otherwise inoffensive citizens. So all drugs should be legal.'}

{'type': 'pro', 'text': "Reducing the number of users and frequency of use is just a means to an end. The end goal is to reduce harms created by drug use. It's perfectly possible to increase use and have less overall harm. So all drugs should be legal."}
{'type': 'con', 'text': 'Because pain is an important clinical symptom, legal recreational opioids may delay patients from seeking care in a timely fashion.'}
{'type': 'con', 'text': 'Education on how to be safe with drugs can be seen as an incentive to use them. I believe drugs should remain illegal.'}
{'type': 'con', 'text': 'Many Canadian cigarettes are [smuggled back](https://www.publicsafety.gc.ca/cnt/rsrcs/pblctns/archive-stts-cntrbnd-tbcc/index-en.aspx) into Canada.'}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': "Criminalization \\(and incarceration\\) causes lasting harm to a person's health and life outcomes."}

{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'The government specifies what is unacceptable through prohibition. Taxation is how the government discourages. The government is only "encouraging" if they provide aid or assistance.'}

{'type': 'pro', 'text': "Kids should learn right from wrong from their parents and communities/churches. What is lawful isn't always right \\(for example: adultery\\). I think legalization of drugs is a pretty good idea."}
{'type': 'con', 'text': 'Allowing people to become addicted merely so we can understand addiction is socially and medically irresponsible. I believe legalization of drugs is a really bad idea.'}

{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'Even a year after release, former convicts [are 10-18 times more likely](https://sph.unc.edu/sph-news/former-inmates-at-high-risk-for-opioid-overdose-following-prison-release/) to die of an overdose than the average population.'}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'Removing some of these constraints through the legalisation of drugs could make studies more successful.'}

{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'Coming from families with unstable backgrounds alone is associated with withdrawal from societal life. It might be the cause of both the withdrawal and the drug use. So all drugs should be legal.'}

{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'If drugs being illegal prevented addiction, there would be no drug addicted person. Thus, there is no prevention by just keeping drugs illegal. So legalization of drugs is a pretty good idea.'}

{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'Regulated, corporate or government sale of these substances should not "target" low income areas and take advantage of disadvantaged people in the same way that current gangs, criminal organizations and other drug dealers currently do.
